article.description: — Kino Lilly Jr. had 22 points, making six 3-pointers, as Brown defeated Central Connecticut 75-57 on Sunday.
article.headline: Lilly Jr. lifts Brown past Central Connecticut 75-57
article.linkText: Lilly Jr. lifts Brown past Central Connecticut 75-57
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- — Kino Lilly Jr. had 22 points, making six 3-pointers, as Brown defeated Central Connecticut 75-57 on Sunday. Lilly drained five 3s during a 32-4 run in the second half that shot the Bears from eight points down into a 64-44 lead in about nine minutes. Paxson Wojcik had 12 points and six rebounds for Brown (2-1). Dan Friday added 11 points. Jaylan Gainey had eight rebounds and eight points. Stephane Ayangma had 14 points for the Blue Devils (0-2). Ian Krishnan added 13 points. Andre Snoddy had seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
